        "text": "The REIQ standard contract requires you to deliver keys, security codes and remote controls for everything included in the sale at settlement. That covers front and back door keys, garage and gate remotes, alarm codes and any keys to outbuildings, letterboxes, pool gates or window locks. In practice this is handled by leaving the keys with your selling agent on or before settlement day, with the agent releasing them to the buyer once your solicitor confirms settlement has been effected and funds have cleared. Manuals, warranties and service records are not strictly required by the contract but are expected by buyers and are part of a normal handover in Brisbane's inner east."
